<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[US Top News and Analysis]]></title><link/> https://www.cnbc.com/us-top-news-and-analysis/ <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/cnbc/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[CNBC is the world leader in business news and real-time financial market coverage. Find fast, actionable information. - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language>英文</language><lastbuilddate>2023 年 5 月 20 日星期六 06:22:34 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Agco CEO says food inflation is here to stay, even if the war in Ukraine ends tomorrow]]></title><description><![CDATA[<span class="HighlightShare-hidden" style="top:0;left:0"><div role="region" aria-labelledby="Placeholder-ArticleBody-Video-107244285"><div role="button" tabindex="0" id="Placeholder-ArticleBody-Video-107244285" class="PlaceHolder-wrapper" data-vilynx-id="7000299991" data-test="VideoPlaceHolder"><div class="InlineVideo-videoEmbed" id="InlineVideo-0" data-test="InlineVideo"><div class="InlineVideo-wrapper"><div class="InlineVideo-inlineThumbnailContainer"><img class="InlineVideo-videoThumbnail" src="https://image.cnbcfm.com/api/v1/image/107244290-1684537785MM-Block-D-short-051923.jpg?v=1684539784&amp;w=750&amp;h=422&amp;vtcrop=y" alt="AGCO CEO Hansotia：即使乌克兰战争结束，该地区也需要一段时间才能种植农作物" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><span class="InlineVideo-videoButton"></span><div class="undefined PlayButton-container" data-test="PlayButton"><div class="PlayButton-featured PlayButton-base" data-type="play"><span class="PlayButton-flyout">现在看</span><span class="icon-play-triangle PlayButton-icon"></span></div></div></div><div class="InlineVideo-videoFooter"><div class="InlineVideo-videoDurationContainer"><span class="InlineVideo-videoLabel">视频</span><span class="InlineVideo-videoDurationWithLeading0">1:18</span> <span class="InlineVideo-videoDuration InlineVideo-videoLabel">01:18</span></div><div class="InlineVideo-title"> AGCO CEO Hansotia：即使乌克兰战争结束，该地区也需要一段时间才能种植农作物</div><div class="InlineVideo-section"><a href="https://www.cnbc.com/mad-money/">与吉姆克莱默一起疯狂赚钱</a></div></div></div></div><div class="PlaceHolder-endCard PlaceHolder-inactive "></div></div></div><div class="group"><p>农业机械制造商<span class="QuoteInBody-quoteNameContainer" data-test="QuoteInBody" id="NewsShowArticle-QuoteInBody-1"><a href="https://www.cnbc.com/quotes/AGCO/">Agco</a></span>的首席执行官 Eric Hansotia <span class="QuoteInBody-quoteNameContainer" data-test="QuoteInBody" id="NewsShowArticle-QuoteInBody-1"><span class="QuoteInBody-inlineButton"><span class="AddToWatchlistButton-watchlistContainer" id="-WatchlistDropdown" data-analytics-id="-WatchlistDropdown"><button class="AddToWatchlistButton-watchlistButton"><span class="AddToWatchlistButton-addWatchListFromTag"></span></button></span></span></span>周五告诉 CNBC 的<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/jim-cramer-bio/">吉姆克莱默</a>，即使俄罗斯对乌克兰的入侵明天结束，谷物价格上涨以及食品成本高企仍将持续。</p><p>俄罗斯和乌克兰都是全球主要粮食供应国，后者常被称为“欧洲粮仓”，2022年2月爆发战争，全球粮食供应链陷入<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2022/02/23/impact-of-russia-ukraine-on-supply-chains-food-metals-commodities.html">动荡</a>。</p><div style="height:100%" class="lazyload-placeholder"></div><p>当 Hansotia <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2022/03/24/agco-ceo-says-russia-ukraine-wars-potential-consequences-on-global-food-supply-is-a-really-big-deal.html">去年 3 月</a>与“Mad Money”坐下来时，他告诉克莱默，当俄罗斯和乌克兰边境关闭时，“全球 13% 的卡路里来自生产”。</p><p> Hansotia 表示，再加上气候问题——即欧洲和北美的干旱——俄罗斯入侵引发的食品供应链灾难不太可能很快消失。</p><p> “即使 [战争] 明天结束，该地区种植作物的能力也会长期下降，因此市场将持续相当长的一段时间，”他说。</p><p>尽管存在谷物供应链问题，但销售拖拉机和联合收割机等大型农业设备的 Agco 最近报告了一个成功的季度。该公司大幅上调全年预测，净销售额达到 33 亿美元，超过市场普遍预期的 31.6 亿美元。</p><p>即便如此，爱科的销售额仍较季后高点下降了约 15%。</p><div style="height:100%" class="lazyload-placeholder"></div><p>但 Hansotia 重申明年对 Agco 产品的强劲需求，强调谷物库存使用率下降以及农民生产成本下降。</p><p> “库存与使用比率——基本上是市场上有多少谷物——已经连续六年下降，”Hansotia 告诉 Cramer。</p><p> “这是表明需求量的最佳指标之一，这是粮食价格的支撑。与此同时，我们农民的投入成本、柴油、化肥和其他东西——实际上正在下降，这些是明年可以锁定的成本。” </p></div><div role="region" aria-labelledby="Placeholder-ArticleBody-Video-107244275"><div role="button" tabindex="0" id="Placeholder-ArticleBody-Video-107244275" class="PlaceHolder-wrapper" data-vilynx-id="7000299989" data-test="VideoPlaceHolder"><div class="InlineVideo-videoEmbed" id="InlineVideo-0" data-test="InlineVideo"><div class="InlineVideo-wrapper"><div class="InlineVideo-inlineThumbnailContainer"><img class="InlineVideo-videoThumbnail" src="https://image.cnbcfm.com/api/v1/image/107244289-1684537522MM-Block-D-051923.jpg?v=1684537765&amp;w=750&amp;h=422&amp;vtcrop=y" alt="Jim Cramer 会见 AGCO 首席执行官 Eric Hansotia" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><div class="nonpremium-investingclub-video" style="z-index:100;position:relative"></div></div><div class="InlineVideo-videoFooter"><div class="InlineVideo-videoDurationContainer"><span class="InlineVideo-videoLabel">视频</span><span class="InlineVideo-videoDurationWithLeading0">8:00</span> <span class="InlineVideo-videoDuration InlineVideo-videoLabel">08:00</span></div><div class="InlineVideo-title"> <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/investingclub/" class="InvestingClubPill-investingClubPillLink" data-type="investing-club-button"><img class="InlineVideo-investingClubPill InvestingClubPill-investingClubPill" src="https://static-redesign.cnbcfm.com/dist/f9ace92fca661c9f3bdf.svg" alt="CNBC 投资俱乐部" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a> Jim Cramer 会见 AGCO 首席执行官 Eric Hansotia</div><div class="InlineVideo-section"><a href="https://www.cnbc.com/mad-money/">与吉姆克莱默一起疯狂赚钱</a></div></div></div></div><div class="PlaceHolder-endCard PlaceHolder-inactive "></div></div></div><div class="group"><div class="RelatedContent-relatedContent" id="NewsShowArticle-RelatedContent-1"><div class="RelatedContent-container"><div class="RelatedContent-nonCollapsibleContent"><h2 class="RelatedContent-header">吉姆克莱默的投资指南</h2><div class="group"><p><a href="https://www.cnbc.com/cramerguide/">单